<Author>btoad1
<Content>Great Place, Great Time Off to a good start from the excellent directions to the hostel. We were booked into our room before check in time. The check in and out times are great, noon check out and 1pm check in. Our train didn't leave on our last night until 10:45pm and we were allowed to leave our luggage in a safe room so we could explore the city and return to use the internet until we were ready to leave for our train. The rooms are clean, safe, colorful and have everything you need from internet, bathtubs, refrigerators to blaconies that over look the streets. Some may say it's too loud or noisy, but that's an unfair review. The staff make sure to provide a comfortable and quiet hostel with double sliding glass doors and thick walls, and anywhere you stay in Madrid that is central city located, you're bound to hear the bass and boom from the clubs till 5am anyways. The closeness to the clubs, bars, shops and attractions as well as the unique setup and feel of this hostel provides enough comfort and exhaustion to drown all that out and sleep comfortably. 
