<Author>alexadams
<Content>Great place for a short stay in Madrid Great hostal in a central location, right next to all the tapas bars, restaurants, and cafes. All the rooms are individually decorated (and IKEA furniture). The room was very clean and tidy. The staff all spoke excelent English and always on hand and helpful. Again like the other reviews find it hard to understand the negative reviews; it's a good hostal and you get value for money.The rooms are quite large, and like most hostals, a small but tidy bathroom. The lift was working well and the hostal has the bonus of being on the top floor so you have a great view over the rooftops, right over to the Plaza Major and beyond. The street does have a few prostitutes hanging about but so does half of Madrid it seems. Don't let that put you off, as the tapas and bars are great. Plus points: The hostal is 100 yards from the Medina Mayrit arabic baths which is must for any visit to the area. Downside: the walls do seem a bit thin so some noise at night is possible. The background noise of Madrid does seem to drown it out though. All in all a good short stay. 
