<Author>cliftonNottingham
<Content>Excellent,central and cheap hostal We are two 70+ year old travellers who stayed here for a week in November. The hostal is on the fourth floor but has an efficient lift and the building has good security. Our room was very clean and bright,warm and en suite. Although it looked out onto the street, it was not noisy at night. Breakfast was available in a restaurant about 10 yards from the front door of the building. The staff on reception were pleasant and helpful and spoke English.It is very centrally located and we were able to walk comfortably to most of the major attractions including the Prado. A short 300-400 yard walk takes you into the Puerto del Sol which has great connections to the excellent underground system.[Be sure to buy books of 10 tickets at a time] There is a wide selection of tapas bars and restaurants in the immediate vicinity of the hostal.We thought it was an excellent place to stay if you do not want the facilities, bar etc of an expensive hotel and are active tourists who do not want to stay in your hotel for most of the day. We find it hard to understand the really negative report which appearsand feel it must be about some other hostal! 
