<Content>Yes, it's excellent We stayed from 16-20 april, in room 112 (alias room # 7 on their webpage, the black-and-white one) and payed 63 euros per night for a perfectly clean room with shower and bath, TV, fridge, air conditioning and windows that did prevent most of this city's immense noise from getting in. Staff was friendly at check-in and check-out, and somewhat invisible during the rest of our stay. We did get fresh towels more than once (yet not on a daily basis, the details remained unclear to us). The elevator was working (even it did not appear to us to be reassuring). Our friend from Madrid once came to pick us up at the hostal and also said he would definitely recommend it to other visitors.It is centrally located, yes, but the nearest cafes, bars and restaurants all seem to welcome mostly tourists. If you head out for something more madrileno, you should not walk down to the Puerta del Sol, but instead walk uphill to the Plaza de Santa Ana and the Calle del Prado, where there is a great variety of places to eat and drink. 
