<Author>tricky-t
<Content>Perfect location for seeing Madrid We paid 63 euro a night to stay at this hostal. I did not request a particular room, so unfortunately, we got the one room I didn't think I would want. It was room 517 at the very end of the hall, with one tiny little window. My parents got the black and white one, 512, which was actually a little bigger than it looked in the pictures. They had a much bigger window. The one advantage to our room was that we did not hear any street noise. This being an older building, however, we could hear our next door neighbors a little and a strange dripping (?) sound at night. It didn't bother me, and my husband just put in earplugs to sleep. The only other complaint we had was one of the pillows was very lumpy. It was not a down pillow like the rest of the others. In any case, I am still glad we stayed at Hostal Adriano because it was the perfect place from which to see all the sights. If you don't mind walking, you can walk to all the sites in Madrid. If you'd rather take the metro, the Sol is the nearest metro stop, and everything is within about 4 stops from there. There are many restaurants and bars within walking distance of the hostal, and plenty of shopping around Puerta del Sol, including El Corte Ingles, which is a department store, book store, supermarket, etc. I highly recommend staying at Hostal Adriano. The elevator works now, so getting up to the 4th floor should not be a problem. If for some reason you have to take the stairs, be careful, as the steps are not evenly spaced, and the stairway can be dark. Another bit of advice - when trying to find the hostal, look up! The signs for the hostal are at the very top of the building. 
