<Content>Perfect for us This is a lovely hostal. (A Spanish hostal is a small, family-owned hotel, not to be confused with a hostel). We booked a double room for three nights at 58 EUR, taxes included. I had read great reviews at the Madridman website, and was not disappointed. It's in the Puerta del Sol area, close to a metro station, and in the middle of everything. The room was smallish, but very clean, with new everything, and tastefully decorated. The tiny bathroom had all new fixtures, including a tub, and was super clean, as the rest of the room. No alarm clock provided, but we found out that the TV has both a clock and an alarm feature! The window/small balcony facing the street had new double sliding glass doors that closed tightly, so we had no street noise problem. This place is highly recommended. The building has an elevator, and many tapas bars/restaurants on the same street. (Best places for a drink or bite are those full of locals.) 
