<Content>Nice, clean, central I have spent 4 nights in this hostal (from 3 to 7 August 2005)As already described in the previous reviews, the hostal is very nicely decorated, very clean and central.The hostal is located in a nice area, full of restaurants, bars and shops. Rooms are equipped with double (=2) windows, so you will not hear anything from the noisy nearby streets.My room was Room 115 (room 10 in the website); it was exactly as you can see it in the hostal website, but for bed covers (mine were white with thin blue and light blue stripes, very nice)The bathroom was very small, but, again, very clean and nicely decorated (orange color). The lift was there, but it was still out of order. 
